#!/opt/venv/bin/python
"""Shimpz gateway — a Telegram bot (voice + text + buttons) whose brain is Claude Code.

  Telegram  ──(voice)──►  OpenAI STT ─┐
            ──(text)──────────────────┼─►  `claude -p` (acting: Bash + toolbelt + Chrome/CDP + shimpz-input vision)
                                       │        │
            ◄── text  ◄────────────────┘        ▼  reply
            ◄── voice note (OpenAI TTS, when you spoke)

Interactive layer:
  • /menu, /desktop, /reset commands + a command menu.
  • Inline buttons for the menu and for APPROVALS / CAPTCHA handoff.
  • IPC bridge: the brain calls `shimpz-approve`/`shimpz-captcha`, which drop a request file in
    $SHIMPZ_HOME/ipc; this gateway watches it, sends inline buttons, and writes back your choice.

Single-user: only TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS may talk to it. Per-chat Claude sessions persist
(via --resume). Launched + supervised by the desktop autostart.
"""

