# --- Memory model: CONTINUITY-PER-CONVERSATION (short-term in session, long-term on disk) --
# A conversation keeps ONE session (--resume, checkpoint-and-rotate past SHIMPZ_CTX_MAX_BYTES) so a long
# task never drags a multi-MB transcript AND never loses its thread — that whole run-core lives in
# shimpzchat.py now (SESSIONS/_prepare_brain_run/_checkpoint_summary, re-exported above). Long-term
# cross-task learnings live in the memory store: shimpz-recall injects them ONLY on a fresh session.
